WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:06.000
This is unit one of Pimsleur's French One.

00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:19.640
Listen to this French conversation.

00:00:19.640 --> 00:00:24.500
In the next few minutes, you'll learn not only to understand this conversation, but

00:00:24.500 --> 00:00:27.160
to take part in it yourself.

00:00:27.160 --> 00:00:31.320
Imagine an American man sitting on a train across from a French woman.

00:00:31.320 --> 00:00:37.359
He wants to begin a conversation, so he says, excuse me.

00:00:37.359 --> 00:00:42.320
The French speaker is going to repeat this part by part, starting from the end.

00:00:42.320 --> 00:00:46.879
You are to repeat each part after him, trying to make your pronunciation sound

00:00:46.879 --> 00:00:48.679
exactly like his.

00:00:48.679 --> 00:00:51.679
Be sure you repeat aloud.

00:00:57.160 --> 00:01:20.159
How do you say excuse me in French?

00:01:21.159 --> 00:01:26.159
Excusez-moi.

00:01:26.159 --> 00:01:29.159
Now he wants to ask her if she understands English.

00:01:29.159 --> 00:01:31.159
First, the word English.

00:01:31.159 --> 00:01:33.159
Listen and repeat.

00:01:33.159 --> 00:01:43.159
L'anglais.

00:01:43.159 --> 00:01:47.159
How do you say English?

00:01:47.159 --> 00:01:50.159
L'anglais.

00:01:50.159 --> 00:01:57.159
Now say the same word, leaving off the L sound at the beginning.

00:01:57.159 --> 00:02:03.159
Anglais.

00:02:03.159 --> 00:02:07.159
Now again with the L sound.

00:02:07.159 --> 00:02:13.159
L'anglais.

00:02:13.159 --> 00:02:19.159
The difference is that when the L sound is off, you're saying English, and when

00:02:19.159 --> 00:02:22.159
it's on, you're saying the English.

00:02:22.159 --> 00:02:27.159
Most of the time, the L sound will be there in French, even when the word the

00:02:27.159 --> 00:02:30.159
is not there in English.

00:02:30.159 --> 00:02:34.159
Once again, say English.

00:02:34.159 --> 00:02:40.159
L'anglais.

00:02:40.159 --> 00:02:45.159
Say excuse me.

00:02:45.159 --> 00:02:53.159
Excusez-moi.

00:02:53.159 --> 00:02:58.159
You should repeat after the speaker gives the right response, trying to make your

00:02:58.159 --> 00:03:01.159
pronunciation sound like his.

00:03:01.159 --> 00:03:04.159
Excusez-moi.

00:03:04.159 --> 00:03:08.159
Say again English.

00:03:08.159 --> 00:03:15.159
L'anglais.

00:03:15.159 --> 00:03:18.159
Now he wants to ask, do you understand?

00:03:18.159 --> 00:03:21.159
Here's the word understand.

00:03:21.159 --> 00:03:23.159
Comprenez.

00:03:23.159 --> 00:03:25.159
Repeat, part by part.

00:03:25.159 --> 00:03:30.159
Né.

00:03:30.159 --> 00:03:35.159
Prenez.

00:03:35.159 --> 00:03:46.159
Comprenez.

00:03:46.159 --> 00:03:50.159
Say understand.

00:03:50.159 --> 00:03:54.159
Comprenez.

00:03:54.159 --> 00:03:56.159
Here's how to say you understand.

00:03:56.159 --> 00:03:58.159
Listen and repeat.

00:03:58.159 --> 00:04:16.159
Vous comprenez.

00:04:16.160 --> 00:04:20.160
Say you understand.

00:04:20.160 --> 00:04:28.160
Vous comprenez.

00:04:28.160 --> 00:04:33.160
Do you remember how to say English?

00:04:33.160 --> 00:04:37.160
L'anglais.

00:04:37.160 --> 00:04:41.160
Say you understand.

00:04:41.160 --> 00:04:45.160
Vous comprenez.

